        "title": "fix(agent): surface non_deliverable_terminal_turn with a specific retry message",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nSurfaces `non_deliverable_terminal_turn` with a specific retry message instead\nof the generic \"Agent couldn't generate a response\" fallback. Fixes #94176.\n\n## Changes\n\n1. **types.ts**: Add `terminalError?: string` to `EmbeddedAgentRunMeta`\n2. **agent-lifecycle-terminal.ts**: Forward `terminalError` through deferred lifecycle keys\n3. **agent-runner-failure-copy.ts**: Resolver `resolveExternalRunFailureTextForTerminalError()` maps the marker to retry-first copy\n4. **attempt.ts** (wiring fix): Return `terminalError` in attempt result\n5. **run.ts** (wiring fix): Include `terminalError` in all 3 incomplete_turn meta blocks\n\n## Proof — Tests pass\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt-trajectory-status.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  225 passed (225)\n```\n\n## Wiring fix details\n\nThe original PR correctly added the type, deferred key, and resolver, but the\ndata was never populated because:\n- `attempt.ts` recorded terminalError only in trajectory events (not the result)\n- `run.ts` did not propagate terminalError into the 3 meta.error blocks\nThis fix closes that gap so downstream reply/followup code can read terminalError\nfrom propagated metadata.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
